[
  {
    "sub_id3": "IEE4936  ",
    "scr_credit": 1.0,
    "sub_name": "實習輔導與職涯發展(一)",
    "sub_ename": "INTERNSHIP ADVISING AND CAREER DEVELOPMENT (1)",
    "describe_ch": "本課程搭配各學士班或研究所之專業實習課程，於學生實習期間，進行個人化實習與職涯輔導，關注實習生的實習安全與預防。引導實習生強化職場倫理與態度、實習之權利義務、性別平等、環境安全衛生等進階觀念，並能了解專業實習實務與職業生涯發展關聯性。與實習生建立聯繫管道，安排時間與實習生晤談，晤談內容得包含職涯規劃、職涯發展、職場不適應或職場倫理等議題，並關切實習適應情形。若遇到實習生身心問題時，得視狀況轉介至專業輔導人員協助之。",
    "describe_en": "This course is paired with an internship course for bachelor’s or graduate’s programs. Personalized advising is executed for internships and careers during the internship. Interns are concerned about the safety and prevention of internships. It also guides interns to strengthen advanced concepts such as workplace ethics and attitudes, rights and duties of internships, gender equality, or environmental, health and safety etc. They understand the relationship between professional practice and career development. To set up contact channels with interns, arrange time for interviews with interns, including career planning, career development, workplace incompatibility, or employment ethics and other issues. To care about internship adaptation. If the interns encounters physical and mental problems, depending on the situation, he or she may be referred to professional counselors for assistance."
  }
]

